Data Description¶

Feature Name Description
age Age in years
sex Gender (0 = female, 1 = male)
bmi Body mass index
bp Average blood pressure
s1 Total serum cholesterol (TC)
s2 Low-density lipoproteins (LDL)
s3 High-density lipoproteins (HDL)
s4 Total cholesterol / HDL ratio (TCH)
s5 Possibly log of serum triglycerides level (LTG)
s6 Blood sugar level (GLU)
In [3]:
data_dictionary = {
    "age": "Age",
    "sex": "Sex",
    "bmi": "Body Mass Index",
    "bp": "Blood Pressure",
    "tc": "Total serum cholestrol",
    "ldl": "Low-density Lipoproteins",
    "hdl": "High-density Lipoproteins",
    "tch": "Total cholestrol",
    "ltg": "Log_serum triglycerides level",
    "glu": "Blood glucose level",
    "y": "y",
}
df = df.rename(
    columns={
        "s1": "tc",
        "s2": "ldl",
        "s3": "hdl",
        "s4": "tch",
        "s5": "ltg",
        "s6": "glu",
    }
)

EDA¶

  1. line, box, q-qplot, heatmap, histplot.

Histogram¶

In [8]:
ncols = 3
selected_col_to_plot = list(set(df.columns) - set(["sex"]))
nrows = int(len(selected_col_to_plot) / ncols) + 1
fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows, ncols)
axs: list[plt.Axes] = axs.flatten()
for i, col in enumerate(selected_col_to_plot):
    sns.histplot(df[col], ax=axs[i])
    axs[i].set_xlabel(data_dictionary[col])
for j in range(i + 1, ncols * nrows):
    fig.delaxes(axs[j])
fig.set_figheight(15)
fig.set_figwidth(15)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("../report/imgs/histogram.svg")
plt.show()

Q-Q Plot¶

In [13]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows, ncols)
fig.set_figheight(15)
fig.set_figwidth(15)
axes: list[plt.Axes] = axes.flatten()
for i, col in enumerate(selected_col_to_plot):
    qqplot(df[col], fit=True, ax=axes[i], line="r", markersize=2)
    axes[i].grid()
    axes[i].set_title(data_dictionary[col])
for j in range(i + 1, nrows * ncols):
    fig.delaxes(axes[j])
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("../report/imgs/qqplot.svg")
plt.show()
